@@ -0,0 +1,254 @@
+NetBSD cells-v2 developer guide (implementation notes)
+======================================================
+
+Status
+------
+This guide reflects the current source tree and runtime behavior.
+
+
+1. Source and module map
+------------------------
+Kernel components:
+- `sys/secmodel/cell/secmodel_cell.c`
+- `sys/secmodel/cell/secmodel_cell_policy.c`
+- `sys/secmodel/cell/secmodel_cell_sysctl.c`
+- `sys/secmodel/cell/cell.h`
+- `sys/sys/cell.h`
+
+Userland components:
+- `usr.sbin/cellctl/cellctl.c`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/cellmgr`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/lib/dispatch.sh`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/lib/cell.sh`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/lib/volume.sh`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/lib/system.sh`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/lib/ipc.sh`
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/lib/common.sh`
+- `usr.sbin/cellui/adapter.c`
+- `usr.sbin/cellui/ui.c`
+
+`cellmgr` load order details:
+- `usr.sbin/cellmgr/cellmgr` defines base functions
+- `load_cellmgr_modules` sources `lib/*.sh`
+- sourced module functions intentionally become the active command handlers
+
+
+2. Command architecture
+-----------------------
+Current top-level dispatch (`dispatch_command`):
+- `ipc`
+- `cell`
+- `volume`
+- `system`
+- `apply`
+- `help`
+
+Design contracts:
+- resource-oriented read verbs: `list|show|fields`
+- mutation domain is explicit via `--scope`
+- read projection is explicit via `--view`
+- machine output is explicit via `-T`/`-H`/`-o`
+
+
+3. Cell snapshot/read pipeline internals
+----------------------------------------
+Key functions:
+- `runtime_collect_snapshot`
+- `runtime_parse_output_fields`
+- `runtime_project_fields`
+- `runtime_list`
+- `runtime_show`
+- `runtime_fields`
+
+Snapshot assembly sources:
+- desired manifests (`MANIFEST_DIR/*.cell`)
+- rendered runtime config (`CELL_DATA_DIR/*/cell.conf`)
+- `cellctl list -T`
+- `cellctl stats -T`
+
+Schema guards:
+- `cellctl list -T` accepts only 6-column or 9-column header variants
+- `cellctl stats -T` must match exact 9-column header
+- any mismatch returns hard error (`runtime: unexpected TSV schema ...`)
+
+Merge result column layout (internal stable order):
+1. `name`
+2. `running`
+3. `desired_state`
+4. `cid`
+5. `refs`
+6. `procs`
+7. `cpu1s`
+8. `cpu10s`
+9. `memory`
+10. `age`
+11. `root`
+12. `autostart`
+13. `create_profile`
+14. `create_reserved_ports`
+15. `create_rlimit_nofile`
+16. `create_rlimit_as`
+17. `create_rlimit_core`
+18. `depends_on`
+19. `healthcheck`
+20. `supervise_cmd`
+21. `volume_mounts`
+22. `manifest`
+23. `rendered`
+24. `apply_present`
+
+
+4. Volume snapshot/read pipeline internals
+------------------------------------------
+Key functions:
+- `volume_collect_snapshot`
+- `volume_parse_output_fields`
+- `volume_project_fields`
+- `volume_list_view`
+- `volume_show_view`
+- `volume_fields_view`
+
+Merged row layout:
+1. `name`
+2. `manifest`
+3. `runtime`
+4. `mode`
+5. `path`
+6. `mounted`
+7. `refs`
+8. `used_by`
+
+Computation notes:
+- `refs` from manifest scan (`volume_ref_count`)
+- `used_by` from manifest mount references (`volume_used_by_list`)
+- `mounted` from mount-table scan (`runtime_volume_mounted`)
+
+
+5. Mutation internals
+---------------------
+Desired state writers:
+- `create_manifest_cell`
+- `set_manifest_cell`
+- `write_manifest_cell_conf_file`
+- `create_manifest_volume`
+- `set_manifest_volume`
+
+Runtime render/mount path:
+- `create_cell`
+- `write_runtime_cell_conf`
+- `mount_cell_root` / `umount_cell_root`
+- `mount_cell_volumes` / `umount_cell_volumes`
+- `setup_local_dev`
+
+Lifecycle actions:
+- `start_cell_internal`
+- `start_cell`, `stop_cell`, `restart_cell`
+- `stop_cell_processes`
+
+Prune paths:
+- `prune_runtime_cell`, `prune_runtime_all`
+- `prune_runtime_volume`, `prune_runtime_volumes`
+
+Backup paths:
+- volumes: `backup_volume`, `restore_volume`, `delete_volume_backup`
+- overlays: `backup_overlay`, `restore_overlay`, `delete_overlay_backup`
+
+
+6. Reconcile/apply internals
+----------------------------
+Entry points:
+- `run_reconcile_command`
+- `reconcile_all`
+- `reconcile_one_cell`
+- `reconcile_volumes`
+
+Dependency ordering:
+- `reconcile_order` performs topological ordering from `CELL_DEPENDS_ON`
+- missing dependency manifests and cycles are hard failures
+
+Cell-level state machine inputs:
+- manifest hash and prior `state/manifest.sha256`
+- apply hash and prior `state/apply.sha256`
+- runtime existence (`cell.conf` presence)
+- running state (`cell_exists`)
+- drift class:
+  - service drift (`autostart`, supervise cmd/log settings, depends, healthcheck, mounts)
+  - policy drift (`create profile`, reserved ports, rlimits)
+
+Notable reconcile behavior:
+- apply plan hash drift triggers `apply_cell_script`
+- autostarted running cell with apply drift is quiesced before plan run
+- policy-only drift warns unless `--restart-changed` is supplied
+- healthcheck runs post-convergence when configured and autostarted
+
+Return semantics:
+- per-cell reconcile returns `2` when changed, `0` when noop, non-zero on failure
+- global `apply --dry-run` returns `2` if any changes are pending
+
+
+7. Declarative plan parser internals
+------------------------------------
+Core parser:
+- `apply_declarative_plan`
+
+Execution helpers:
+- `apply_exec_in_cell`
+- `apply_write_block_file`
+- `apply_patch_block`
+
+Parser contracts:
+- uppercase directive enforcement
+- explicit block state machine for `FILE_BEGIN/FILE_END` and `PATCH_BEGIN/PATCH_END`
+- strict option parsing for `DIR`, `FILE_BEGIN`, `PATCH_BEGIN`
+- package token validation in `validate_pkg_name`
+
+Runtime notes:
+- `apply_cell_script` ensures cert store refresh via `certctl rehash`
+- stopped cells use `--ephemeral` path when applying with autostart `NO`
+
+
+8. IPC internals (`ipc serve --stdio`)
+--------------------------------------
+Server path:
+- `run_ipc_resource_command`
+- `run_ipc_serve_command`
+- `ipc_serve_stdio`
+
+Protocol helpers:
+- `ipc_send_frame_file`
+- `ipc_read_payload`
+- `ipc_execute_call`
+
+Protocol constraints:
+- framed header format: `M 1 <TYPE> <ID> <P1> <P2> <P3> <LEN>`
+- payload hard limit: `67108864` bytes (64 MiB)
+- CALL mode `0` captures stdout/stderr, mode `1` binds command I/O to `/dev/tty`
+- optional single env override is validated (`[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*`)
+
+
+9. `cellui` integration internals
+---------------------------------
+Bridge and protocol client:
+- `usr.sbin/cellui/adapter.c`
+
+Cell list parser contract:
+- command uses fixed `-o` field order with 18 columns
+- parser uses `split_tsv_fixed(..., 18)` and strict bool decoding
+
+Storage parser contract:
+- volumes from 8-column merged volume TSV
+- overlays synthesized from 4-column cell TSV (`name,manifest,running,root`)
+
+Operational behavior:
+- prefers long-lived IPC session
+- on transport failure marks bridge disconnected and surfaces reconnect UI
+
+
+10. Developer guardrails
+------------------------
+- Keep `cellctl -T` schema validation strict and fail-closed.
+- Keep exported field names lowercase `snake_case` and stable.
+- Preserve human-table default for read commands.
+- Keep machine output contracts stable (`-T`, headers, field order with `-o`).
+- Preserve confirmation gates for destructive paths (`--all`, `--orphans`, restore/delete).
+- Maintain name and mount-spec validators as single sources of truth.
